23. Regions, Region Pairs, Sovereign Regions
🌐 Regions

👉 A Region is a physical location where Microsoft Azure has data centers.
✔ Example: India Central, East US

💡 Meaning: “Where your cloud resources are hosted”

🔗 Region Pairs

👉 Each region is paired with another nearby region for backup and disaster recovery.
✔ If one region fails, data can be recovered from its pair.

💡 Example:

East US ↔ West US
🏛️ Sovereign Regions

👉 Special isolated regions for government or regulated data.
✔ Very strict security and compliance.

💡 Example:

US Gov regions
China regions
🏢 24. Availability Zones & Data Centers
🏗️ Data Center

👉 A physical building with servers storing cloud data.

⚡ Availability Zones (AZ)

👉 Separate data centers inside a region.
✔ Each zone is independent (power, network, cooling)

💡 Meaning:

If one zone fails, others still work

📦 25. Resources and Resource Groups
🧩 Resources

👉 Individual cloud items like:

Virtual machines
Databases
Storage accounts
📁 Resource Groups

👉 A container to organize resources together.

💡 Example:
A project may have:

VM
Storage
Database
👉 All stored in one resource group
💳 26. Subscriptions

👉 A billing and access boundary in Azure.

✔ Defines:

Who can use resources
How billing is done

💡 Meaning:

“Your cloud account plan”

🏢 27. Management Groups

👉 A higher-level structure to manage multiple subscriptions.

✔ Used by large organizations
✔ Helps apply policies across all subscriptions

🧠 Simple hierarchy
Management Groups
   ↓
Subscriptions
   ↓
Resource Groups
   ↓
Resources (VM, DB, etc.)
🎯 Final summary
Region = location
Region Pair = backup region
Availability Zone = separate data centers
Resource Group = folder for resources
Subscription = billing/account unit
Management Group = manages multiple subscriptions